Simplifying gives us:
\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{(2-x)(3-x)(4-x)}{-1} + \frac{1}{4} \frac{(1-x)(3-x)(4-x)}{-1} + \frac{1}{9} \frac{(1-x)(2-x)(4-x)}{-1} + \frac{1}{16} \frac{(1-x)(2-x)(3-x)}{-1} \\
&=  - (2-x)(3-x)(4-x) - \frac{1}{4} (1-x)(3-x)(4-x) - \frac{1}{9} (1-x)(2-x)(4-x) - \frac{1}{16} (1-x)(2-x)(3-x)  \\
&=  - (2-x)(3-x)(4-x) - \frac{1}{4} a(x) - \frac{1}{9} b(x) - \frac{1}{16} c(x)
\end{align*}
 Let's denote $a(x) = (1-x)(3-x)(4-x)$, $b(x) = (1-x)(2-x)(4-x)$ and $c(x) = (1-x)(2-x)(3-x)$.
